FBIS3-14826 "drsov039_b_94037" FBIS-SOV-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Feb 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yeltsin Appoints CIS Assembly Envoy LD2502135094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1306 GMT 25 Feb 94 LD2502135094 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Moscow February 25 TASS -- President Boris Yeltsin appointed Sergey Tsiplyayev his plenipotentiary representative at the Interparliamentary Assembly of the Commonwealth of Independent States. Yeltsin's decree notes that the appointment was prompted by the need for maintaining permanent relations between the Russian president and the Interparliamentary Assembly of the CIS states. ITAR-TASS learnt at the presidential press service on Friday that Tsiplyayev, the president's representative in St. Petersburg, will perform his new duties concurrently. The decree provides for setting up an office (which will be a component part of the president's staff) to ensure the operation of the president's representative at the Interparliamentary Assembly.
